title: Mining baron Reddy to return to BJP today
Cash-hit K’taka Cong pins hopes on parents to foot kin’s poll bills

description: Akhil, Lurinjyoti campaigned for AJP in Moran town. Akhil's leadership of Raijor Dal, criticism of Citizenship Amendment Act energized the campaign, receiving overwhelming support from locals.
title: Protest against CAA brings together Akhil and Lurinjyoti in Dibrugarh

description: BJP said it would approach the Election Commission seeking action against Radhakrishnan after he used expletives against Modi at a public rally. Calling DMK MP Kanimozhi a pseudo-feminist as she was on the stage and did not protest, BJP leaders shared the clip on social media in which the minister purportedly used an expletive in Tamil.
title: DMK mantri's rant against PM Modi, Sanatan Dharma draws BJP fire
Day after raids, Mahua asks EC for poll curbs on central agencies
Maharashtra MLA quits Congress for Sena, in line for ticket
BSP fields Rajendra Singh Solanki from Gautam Budh Nagar, Abid Ali
Congress vows SC/ST/OBC quota in private higher educational institutes

description: At a time when Bengaluru is reeling under severe water crisis, a 75-year-old retired army officer strapped on his shoes and set off to live his dream 18,000km away amidst penguins and humpback whales on sheets of ice. On Feb 14, Lt Col (retd) Upendra Kalyan left his hometown for a rendezvous with Antarctic islands. He was one of the only 10 from a group of 140 expeditioners to dare to back-dive into the frigid waters of the Atlantic Ocean.
title: Chilled out: Ex-armyman, 75, goes on Antarctica adventure

description: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar's JD(U) dropped two sitting MPs and picked a pair of turncoats, both of whom joined the party recently, in a list of 16 Lok Sabha candidates announced on Sunday. Former MP and gangster-politician Anand Mohan's wife, Lovely Anand, was fielded in the Sheohar seat within days of jumping ship. Vijayalaxmi Devi, who joined JD(U) on Saturday, got the ticket for Siwan.
title: JD(U) releases list of 16, drops 2 MPs, picks pair of turncoats

description: Freedom of religion should be respected in the country, said Archbishop of Verapoly Joseph Kalathiparambil in a statement issued by public relations department of the archdiocese of Verapoly in Kerala on Sunday. The archbishop called for continued prayers so that the upcoming elections take place as per God's will. He also called for prayers for a governing system in the country, which would uphold human dignity, and is bound to ensure justice, equality and fraternity.
title: Freedom of religion should be respected: Kerala church

description: Bangalore Water Supply and Sewerage Board (BWSSB) has collected 1.1 lakh in fines in three days from 22 cases of violations related to using potable water from Cauvery river and borewells for car wash. BWSSB issued a notice on March 10, informing the public of a fine of 5,000 for each violation of potable water use. It specified activities for which potable water is banned, such as car washing, gardening, and large construction projects.
title: In 3 days, 22 fined 1.1L for washing cars with potable water in B'luru

description: Congress’s promise of creating 30 lakh new jobs in the central govt is part of an elaborate plan the party has worked out for women’s empowerment.The ‘Yuva Nyay’ of 2024 manifesto pledges that if voted to power, Congress govt will create 30 lakh new jobs besides giving “assured first job” to youth below 25 years through year-long apprenticeship in private and public companies.
title: Women at centre of Congress' 30 lakh new jobs' Lok Sabha poll pledge
Citizenship Act supersedes passport rules: High court
Bharat Biotech begins clinical trials of more effective TB vaccine in India

description: Vinod Kumar, a 40-year-old contractor, distraught by the loss of his children and the lack of clarity about the motive behind the crime, said, "I am not concerned with the encounter of the accused or the arrest of the accomplice. All I want to know is why were my children killed."
title: ‘Shoddy probe’, says father of kids murdered in Budaun

description: Dr Pravesh Dhamane and Dr Maniklal Raut were found "reeking of alcohol" on duty and a bottle containing around 180ml leftover liquor was recovered from their car, police said. Various sections of Maharashtra Prohibition Act have been invoked against them. Their blood samples have been collected and sent for testing to Regional Forensic Science Laboratory in Nagpur.
title: 2 govt docs ‘reeking of alcohol’ at hospital in dry Wardha booked
After arrest of IIT-G student for 'IS links', hunt on for another
Mobile charger sparks fire, 4 Uttar Pradesh kids burnt alive

description: A day after two additional SPs were arrested for their alleged roles in surveillance of chief minister A Revanth Reddy and other opposition leaders when BRS was in govt in Telangana, Hyderabad police on Sunday issued look out circulars (LOCs) against former Special Intelligence Bureau (SIB) chief T Prabhakar Rao and former deputy commissioner of police (task force) Radha Kishan in the case.
title: Phone-tapping: Look out circulars against 2 ex-top cops
Chandrayaan-3 landing site now officially called 'Shiva Shakti'

description: Orissa HC has given Kendrapada district collector Suryawanshi Mayur Vikas one month to make arrangements for the disbursal of family pension to a 91-year-old woman whose husband, a school teacher, died 46 years back. The direction comes four months after HC asked the Kendrapada district collector to sanction family pension to Hara Sahoo, whose husband passed away on Aug 26, 1977.
title: For 46 years, Odisha widow, now 91, waiting for pension

description: 33-year-old, Cheistha Kochhar was killed after being hit by a lorry while cycling back home on March 19. Her husband, Prashant, a software engineer, was a few yards ahead of her on his bike when the accident occurred. He heard a loud thud and rushed back to help Cheistha. Police officers and paramedics rushed to the spot and found her seriously injured. She died soon after.
title: Indian PhD student at LSE killed on bike in London

description: A 23-year-old man from Gandhinagar has been indicted in a case of ponzi scam worth $4,00,000 in Alabama in the US. The accused, Pathyam Patel, began selling securities without registration and kept collecting money after guaranteeing huge returns which he never invested in securities. Instead, he used them to meet his personal expenses.
title: Gandhinagar man held in US for ponzi scam worth $4,00,000
Jobless couple pose as NIA sleuths, abduct woman; nabbed
IAF ex-chief RKS Bhadauria in BJP on day VK Singh leaves fray

description: Four days after the first deaths were reported following the consumption of spurious liquor in Gujjran village of Dirba in Punjab's Sangrur district, chief minister Bhagwant Mann and finance minister and Dirba MLA Harpal Cheema on Sunday visited the families of the victims at the village. The death toll has already climbed to 21. Around 20 others are undergoing treatment at hospitals.
title: Mann meets kin of Punjab hooch tragedy victims, promises action

description: Border Roads Organisation has reopened Zoji La (pass), the main obstacle in Ladakh's lifeline via Srinagar, for vehicular traffic after 35 days of being under snow against 68 days last year - a record that reflects India's growing mountain road-building prowess that has big upside for border defence as well as people's lives in the frontier region.
title: In a record, Zoji La reopens after 35 days against 68 in 2023

description: BJP on Sunday decided to field Naveen Jindal, who heads steel and power giant JSPL, from Kurukshetra, hours after he switched over to the saffron party. Jindal — an accused in the coal scam, which was a key election issue for BJP in 2014 — was twice elected to Lok Sabha from Kurukshetra. In 2014, he had finished third when BJP’s Raj Kumar Saini won, and was not fielded by Congress in the 2019 polls.
title: Naveen Jindal gets ticket hours after quitting Congress

description: With BJP basking in the glory of fulfilling one of its oldest promises of building Ram Temple in Ayodhya, Arun Govil, an actor who played Lord Ram in the popular ‘Ramayan’ serial, is in the list of the party’s 111 Lok Sabha candidates announced on Sunday. Actor Kangana Ranaut, a staunch advocate of Hindutva, has been named from Himacha’s Mandi, where she takes on Congress state president and incumbent MP Pratibha Singh .
title: Kangana, Cal HC ex-judge, Sita Soren, Jitin Prasada in BJP 5th list

description: Dar's statement about ending the nearly five-year suspension of trade over India revoking J&K's special status in August 2019 comes weeks after PM Shehbaz Sharif thanked counterpart Narendra Modi for his congratulatory message on X. India, however, believes Pakistan must first reinstate its high commissioner in India before nursing any thought of a rapprochement with India.
title: Ready to consider resuming India trade ties: Pak minister

description: Mumbai Indians maintained the tradition of losing their opening match of IPL since 2012 with Gujarat Titans snatching an improbable six-run victory in a thrilling match in Ahmedabad on Sunday. While Jasprit Bumrah bowled a couple of terrific spells to restrict Gujarat Titans to 168 for 6 in 20 overs, MI lost their way after Rohit Sharma's dismissal to end up on 162 for 9 in 20 overs.
title: IPL: MI's first match jinx continues after loss to GT
Mughal emperors celebrated Holi as Eid-e-Gulabi, says ASI ex-director

description: Isro awarded for Chandrayaan-3 Moon landing at the South Pole. 'Station Shiv Shakti' approved for the site. Pragyan rover conducted lunar experiments. PM Modi named the site 'Shiv Shakti'. Gazetteer describes planetary features.
title: Isro gets US aviation award for Chandrayaan-3 mission

description: The festival of colours -'Holi' is the most enchanting and colourful tradition in India. It is a festival that carries the universal message of love, togetherness, and joy. In 2024, Holi will be celebrated on 25th March. The day awaits us to immerse ourselves in the vibrancy of colours. It is a festival dedicated to the beauty of colours and symbolises renewal, a beacon of hope, and merriment.
title: 75+ Happy Holi messages, greetings, wishes and quotes for 2024

description: Congress replaced Sunil Sharma with Pratap Singh Khachariyavas for Jaipur seat amid controversy over alleged links to Jaipur Dialogues. Sharma denied claims and criticized propaganda, emphasizing his role as a panelist on news and YouTube channels.
title: Congress drops Jaipur Lok Sabha poll candidate Sunil Sharma amid row

description: The festival of colours-'Holi' is on the horizon. The preparations for Holi have begun with marketplaces decorated with colours of Holi and pichkari.  The onset of the summer season can be felt with the celebration of Holi. A spectrum of colours is the essence of this festival. Holi is one of the biggest festivals of Hindus and is greatly celebrated all over India and also by the Indian diaspora all across the world. A celebration of colours, Holi encompasses all celebratory spirits and moments of togetherness. Also, this Holi, promise yourself an eco-friendly celebration of Holi!
title: Happy Holi 2024: Wishes, messages, quotes, images

description: The fans seemed to have given Hardik Pandya a chilly reception as he made his debut as captain for the Mumbai Indians against the Gujarat Titans at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad on Sunday. During the toss, when Ravi Shastri introduced the captains, Pandya was met with boos from the fans. Even after winning the toss, they continued to jeer at him when he began to speak.
title: 'Never seen any...': KP on Pandya being booed by crowd

description: The Congress released its fifth list on Sunday comprising three candidates for the forthcoming Lok Sabha elections. Congress leader Pratap Singh Khachariyawas will now be contesting from Rajasthan’s Jaipur Lok Sabha constituency, replacing Sunil Sharma, while Murari Lal Meena has been nominated from Dausa, an ST constituency. Congress released the fourth list of 46 candidates on Saturday.

title: Israel besieges 2 more Gaza hospitals, Palestinians demand their evacuation,

description: For Rajasthan Royals, Sanju Samson smashed an unbeaten 82 in 52 balls in their total of 193 for four. The RR skipper led from the front and struck three fours and six sixes while adding 93 runs for the third wicket with Riyan Parag (43). In reply, Nicholas Pooran's unbeaten 64 off 41 balls went in vain as LSG finished 20 runs short.
title: IPL: Samson stars in Rajasthan's win over Lucknow

description: BSP released diverse candidate lists for UP Lok Sabha elections, featuring women candidates and individuals from various communities. The party's selection strategy aimed to represent a wide range of castes and religions, avoiding dependency on specific communities.
title: BSP declares another list of candidates for Lok Sabha elections in UP

description: A four-year-old girl was allegedly raped by brother of her tuition teacher in east Delhi's Pandav Nagar, sparking a protest in the area, police said on Sunday. They said the alleged incident happened on Saturday and the victim has been referred to All All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS)-Delhi from Lal Bahadur Shastri Hospital. The victim's family members and scores of other people gathered outside the house of the accused in protest, demanding strict action against him.
title: 4-year-old raped in Delhi by tuition teacher's brother, protest erupts

description: Interior minister Naqvi stresses the importance of updating internet speech laws amidst ongoing disruptions to platform X, balancing free expression and preventing misuse in Pakistan.
title: What Pakistan minister has to say on long social media ban

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar affirmed Article 370's temporary nature, stating it hindered progressive laws in Jammu, Kashmir, and Ladakh. Speaking in Singapore, he highlighted the benefits of its revocation, citing its role in fostering separatism and violence. The government revoked Article 370 on August 5, 2019, integrating Jammu and Kashmir into two Union Territories.
title: 'Art 370 prevented extension of progressive laws to J&K and Ladakh'

description: Pakistan Cricket Board  chairman Mohsin Naqvi on Sunday reiterated the commitment to hold the Champions Trophy as scheduled in Pakistan. India had refused to send its team for the Asia Cup last year in August which led to a number of matches being moved to Sri Lanka. The 2025 Champions Trophy marks Pakistan's return to hosting an ICC tournament for the first time since it co-hosted a portion of the 1996 World Cup with India.
title: 'Why are we even discussing...': PCB on India's participation in CT

description: An IIT-Guwahati student who had allegedly pledged allegiance to ISIS was arrested under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act on Sunday, a senior official said. The accused Touseef Ali Farooqui, who is a 4th-year student of Bioscience, was detained on Saturday. Assam Police's Special Task Force (STF) Inspector General Parthasarathi Mahanta told PTI that after interrogating him, police found credible evidence of his links with ISIS and he was arrested.
title: IIT-Guwahati student arrested under UAPA for 'links with Isis'
TN MP attempts suicide, kin say he consumed 'sulphas' insecticide

description: Russian forces strike Ukraine's power and gas facilities, launching missiles and drones. Lviv's governor reports hits on critical infrastructure. Polish army confirms missile breach, demands explanation from Moscow.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Sunday greeted people on the eve of Holi. In a post on X, Modi addressed them as his family members and wished that the festival associated with affection and harmony bring new energy and enthusiasm in everyone's life.
title: PM Modi extends greetings on Holi eve

description: The Congress workers in Uttar Pradesh are "confident" that either former party president Rahul Gandhi or general secretary Priyanka Gandhi Vadra will contest the Lok Sabha elections from either Amethi or Raebareli, party state unit chief Ajay Rai said on Sunday. Rai's remarks come a day after the Congress released a list of nine candidates from UP, without naming the candidates for Amethi or Raebareli seats, which were considered family bastions of the Nehru-Gandhis.
title: 'Cong workers sure Gandhis will contest from Amethi or Raebareli'

description: Nasa has now said: “...Nisar is nearly complete… Work to be finished before launch includes applying a special coating to hardware components on the satellite’s 39-foot-diameter (12-metre) radar antenna reflector, which is among Nasa’s primary contributions to the mission.” The addition of the special coating is a precautionary step to mitigate any temperature increases that could potentially affect the deployment of the reflector.
title: Nisar reflector going back to US for additional coating: Nasa

description: It was a spidercam error, as the cable wire fell on the outfield soon after the two balls were bowled into Rajasthan Royals-Lucknow Super Giants IPL match. The engineers swiftly responded to the situation, rushing onto the ground to retrieve the fallen wire of the spidercam and remove it from the field of play.
title: Spidercam halts RR-LSG IPL clash for a brief period

description: Shah Rukh Khan, the co-owner of Kolkata Knight Riders, was left awestruck by Andre Russell's outstanding all-round performance in KKR's inaugural match of IPL 2024 against Sunrisers Hyderabad. Khan openly praised Russell after the match, showcasing his deep admiration for the player's remarkable display.
title: Watch: SRK embraces Russell with a warm hug during victory lap

description: Ayodhya, the sacred city in Uttar Pradesh, is set for a grand Holi celebration this year, honoring Lord Ram. The head priest of the Ram Janmabhoomi Temple, Acharya Satyendra Das, said that just as the devotees gathered after Lord Ram's pran pratishtha, similarly, this year's Holi festivities will be equally joyous in their own unique way.

description: Russia launched its third missile strike on Ukraine, targeting Kyiv for the second time. Poland reported a brief breach of its airspace by a Russian cruise missile. Kyiv was on high alert as rockets approached from the north. No casualties were reported. Poland demanded an explanation from Moscow, emphasizing an end to the conflict.

description: Bengaluru's recent viral scooter video has ignited safety discussions and highlighted work pressure. Social media reactions varied from jokes to frustrations, touching on technical software issues and nostalgia for simpler times.

description: AAP's Gopal Rai announces 'maha rally' at Ramlila Maidan on March 31 to protect democracy post Delhi CM's ED arrest. Arvinder Singh Lovely highlights opposition's challenges and calls to save democracy against BJP-led Centre.
title: INDIA bloc to hold 'maha rally' in Delhi on March 31

description: Sunil Sharma, the Congress's Lok Sabha candidate in Jaipur, has refuted any connection with the Jaipur Dialogues platform, dismissing the allegations as "completely false." The controversy arose on social media, where users pointed out that Sunil Sharma serves as a director for Jaipur Dialogues, known for its critical stance against Congress.

description: Mitchell Starc's underwhelming performance in a match against Sunrisers Hyderabad raised concerns despite the Kolkata Knight Riders' tense 4-run win. Starc struggled against the SRH batters, leaking 53 runs in his four-over spell. His economy rate of 13.20 and six wide deliveries highlighted his struggles on the field.

description: Nearly seven months after Prime Minister Narendra Modi announced (Aug 26, 2023) that the Chandrayaan-3 landing site will be called ‘Shiva Shakti’, the International Astronomical Union (IAU), on March 19 approved the name .According to the Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature, which provides detailed information about planetary names approved by IAU.

description: Andre Russell's stellar all-around display was instrumental in Kolkata Knight Riders clinching a heart-stopping victory by four runs against the Sunrisers Hyderabad in a thrilling IPL encounter on Saturday. Russell's explosive batting guided KKR to a commanding total of 208/7, as he remained unbeaten with a blistering 64 runs off a mere 25 balls. His innings was buoyed by a pivotal 81-run partnership alongside Rinku Singh, setting the stage for Kolkata's imposing total.

Cricketing legend Sachin Tendulkar praised Rana's courage and tactical brilliance, while also praising the contributions of Russell, Klaasen, and Kolkata's Phil Salt, who played pivotal roles in shaping the match's outcome.

Rana's actions resulted in fines of 10% and 50% of his match fees. He admitted to the infractions and accepted the sanctions imposed by the Match Referee.

description: Sophia fell victim to a scam trying to return spoilt milk bought online. The fraudster posed as a grocery platform executive, making her enter UPI PIN, resulting in a loss of Rs 77,000.

description: Assam Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma has stated that Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal may have intentionally provoked his own arrest by repeatedly ignoring Enforcement Directorate summonses related to a money laundering case associated with the now-defunct Delhi liquor policy. Sarma suggested that Kejriwal's actions, including disregarding nine summonses, seemed like a strategic move to gain sympathy and possibly invite arrest.

KKR skipper Shreyas Iyer admitted to feeling jitters as SRH's Heinrich Klaasen fought hard to chase a target of 209 runs. With SRH needing 13 runs off the final over, the odds seemed to favor SRH.
